definition: surname Ji/abbr. for Jilin Province 吉林省[Ji2 lin2 Sheng3]
car/vehicle/CL:輛|辆[liang4]/machine/to shape with a lathe/Kangxi radical 159

sentences.english: Someone brought cold cuts, dark bread, and beer from the jeep.
sentences.chinese: 有人把吉普車上的凍肉，黑麪包和啤酒送上來。

sentences.english: Another survivor, a jeepney driver, lost his vehicle.
sentences.chinese: 另一名災民，又損失了他工作用的吉普車。

sentences.english: Jeepneys are a familiar sight on the streets of Manila.
sentences.chinese: 載客吉普車是馬尼拉街頭的常見景觀。

sentences.english: I don't know which is the bigger piece of shit, you or your Landrover .
sentences.chinese: 我不知道什麼是更大的狗屎，是你還是你的吉普車。

sentences.english: These are jeeps. Those are buses.
sentences.chinese: 這些是吉普車，那些是公共汽車。

sentences.english: A few of the jeeps had run out of ammunition.
sentences.chinese: 幾輛吉普車上的彈藥已經用光了。

sentences.english: Smith borrowed a jeep from Taplett and drove on up to Koto -ri.
sentences.chinese: 史密斯從泰伯利特那裏借了一輛吉普車開到了古土裏。

sentences.english: Our jeep was bumping up and down as we drove along the mountain trail.
sentences.chinese: 我們開在山路上，我們的吉普車一路顛簸而行。

sentences.english: We took two jeeps to go into the huge safari park.
sentences.chinese: 我們搭乘兩輛吉普車，進入了廣闊的野生動物園。

sentences.english: I have Whitetail very close to me and move back to the jeep.
sentences.chinese: 我把白尾巴拉近了十點兒，退向吉普車。

sentences.english: These are jeeps. Those are heavy-duty trucks.
sentences.chinese: 這些是吉普車，那些是載重汽車。

sentences.english: Take a bus or jeep on to Kathmandu.
sentences.chinese: 搭汽車或吉普車到加都。

sentences.english: George drove his jeep across a large bridge.
sentences.chinese: 喬治架着他的吉普車穿過了那座大橋。

sentences.english: I was parked in front of the church cleaning out my Jeep. I was waiting on someone.
sentences.chinese: 我把我的吉普車停靠在教堂前擦洗，邊洗邊等人。

sentences.english: He hypoed his jeep's power by changing a bigger engine.
sentences.chinese: 他爲他的吉普車換了一個更大的發動機以增大其馬力。
